        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 14. Halecium banyulense Motz-Kossowska, 1911, after MHNG INVE 34237. (A) Colony silhouette (scale bar: 1 cm); (B) internode from monosiphonic part (scale bar: 0.2 mm); (C) hydrothecae with regenerated hydrothecae of second and higher degree (scale bar: 0.1 mm); (D) female gonotheca, drawn opaque to visualize radiating depressions (same scale bar as B)." ;
